## For Microsoft 365 Co-Pilot, evaluate Research capability for functional requirement category of Report Generation where Requirement is Summarize lengthy information into concise and clear sections.

### Response: Microsoft 365 Copilot demonstrates robust capabilities for summarizing lengthy information into concise and clear sections:

Available: Copilot can instantly summarize long documents in Word, distilling key points from large reports. It can generate summary slides or executive summaries from lengthy PowerPoint presentations. In Excel, Copilot can analyze spreadsheet data and summarize trends and insights in plain language.

Planned: Copilot in OneDrive will soon allow users to select multiple files (up to five) and get an AI-generated summary or comparison without manually opening them. Copilot in Microsoft Stream will enable users to summarize video content, including recorded meetings or lectures.

These features leverage advanced natural language processing to provide concise, contextually relevant summaries across various content types within the Microsoft 365 ecosystem.

