## For Microsoft 365 Co-Pilot, evaluate Iterative Writing Capability for functional requirement category of Core Iterative Writing Experience where Requirement is Maintain consistency in terminology and style, spelling out acronyms once, then using short-hand, and using a unified voice (e.g., "We" vs. "Accenture" vs. "AFS").

### Response: Microsoft 365 Copilot offers capabilities for maintaining consistency in terminology and style, with plans for further enhancements.

Available: Copilot can maintain consistency in terminology and style through its context-aware generation, adapting to the user's writing preferences and document context. It can follow instructions to use specific terminology or voice consistently throughout a document.

Planned: Microsoft is developing more granular personalization settings, including the ability to define preferred formatting and style defaults, which may enhance Copilot's ability to maintain consistent terminology and voice across documents.

These features enable users to create documents with consistent terminology and style, with planned improvements to offer even more precise control over writing conventions.

Citations:
[Introducing Microsoft 365 Copilot – your copilot for work - The Official Microsoft Blog]
[Introducing Microsoft Copilot Studio and new features in Copilot for Microsoft 365 | Microsoft 365 Blog]

