## For Microsoft 365 Co-Pilot, evaluate Iterative Writing Capability for non-functional requirement category of Security where Requirement is Data encryption in transit and at rest.

### Response: Microsoft 365 Copilot incorporates robust data encryption measures to protect sensitive information during iterative writing processes.

Available: Copilot automatically inherits and applies the organization's existing security policies, including data encryption in transit and at rest. All Copilot interactions are subject to the same encryption standards as other Microsoft 365 data.

Planned: Integration with Microsoft Purview for enhanced compliance auditing and risk detection related to Copilot activities is planned for Q1 2025.

These capabilities ensure that Copilot maintains strong data protection standards during iterative writing tasks, with further enhancements to security and compliance features on the horizon.

Citations:
[Introducing Microsoft 365 Copilot – your copilot for work - The Official Microsoft Blog]
[Microsoft 365 Copilot - Service Descriptions | Microsoft Learn]

