## For Microsoft 365 Co-Pilot, evaluate Iterative Writing Capability for non-functional requirement category of Interoperability where Requirement is Easy integration with third-party tools and services.

### Response: Microsoft 365 Copilot offers growing capabilities for third-party integrations in iterative writing, with significant expansions planned.

Available: Copilot Studio allows organizations to create custom AI agents that can integrate with Copilot, enabling some level of third-party tool connection for writing tasks.

Planned: Microsoft plans to introduce API plugins for custom agents, allowing them to perform actions or retrieve data via external REST APIs. Additionally, Graph Connectors (CY2025) and Power Platform connectors (2025) will expand Copilot's ability to integrate with external data sources and third-party applications for more diverse writing scenarios.

These features demonstrate Copilot's evolving interoperability for iterative writing, with more robust third-party integrations on the horizon.

